00:48:17.040 --> 00:48:18.919
Readr also does this.

00:48:18.919 --> 00:48:24.139
It also supports the inline creation of a data frame.

00:48:24.139 --> 00:48:29.760
It does it through its primary argument, so you would want to read the help for read underscore

00:48:29.760 --> 00:48:43.040
csv, but in fact, it's actually sort of even a smaller departure from your usual use.

